"Kennedy" is a news panel show hosted by Kennedy Montgomery. Kennedy Montgomery is a libertarian that you may recognize from 90's MTV, Stossel, and the Independents.

Kennedy does her monologue on Obama, Iraq, and ISIS.

RAND PAUL is here via satellite to talk about Obama, Iraq, and ISIS. Rand talks glowingly about Kurdish independence.  He also says that he wants no boots on the ground. Next up they talk about the NSA and Paul's growing anti-surveillance coalition. 

Tonights panel consists of JIM NORTON, BEN DOMENECH, CARLEY SHIMKUS. The first thing they talk about is Bill Clinton's promise to stop giving speeches if Hillary wins the race.

MONTEL WILLIAMS is here to talk about a bill in Pennsylvania that allows medical marijuana to be provided to seriously ill patients. Montel Williams is a big fan as is Kennedy. Someone they're not a fan of is State Representative Baker who is single handedly stopping this bill from passing.

TOPICAL STORM:
Massive preggers shark.
Cicadas attack reporter, she quickly freaks out when one lands on her face.
Baseball man gets mad, starts throwing clothes at other players.
Tornado girl.
Pizza hut to stuff delicious hot dogs inside of crust. Only 3,600 calories per pie.

The panel returns to talk about nobel prize winning scientist Tim Hunt who recently got in trouble about some not so PC comments made about women in science. Next topic - monkeys (chimps) observed getting drunk off fermented tree sap. In the first 3 months of this year 1336 people denounced their citizenship. High taxes listed as being the primary reason. 

BILL BELLAMY here to talk about the 90's, Crystal Pepsi revival, Mike n' Ikes, Coolio, Bill Clinton, Seinfeld's recent comments.

Mailbag.
